-- Kevin Davies Signs One-Year Contract to Stay at Relegated Bolton
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2012-05-18T11:29:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-18/kevin-davies-signs-one-year-contract-to-stay-at-relegated-bolton.html
Bolton captain  Kevin Davies  signed 
a one-year contract to remain with the club after it was
relegated from the Premier League.   Davies, 35, agreed to a ninth season as Bolton prepares for
the second-tier Championship, while defender Sam Rickets signed
a two-year contract until 2014, the team said on its website.  Midfielder Nigel Reo-Coker has activated a release clause
in his contract and Gretar Steinsson, Paul Robinson, Sean Davis,
Robbie Blake, Ricardo Gardner,  Ivan Klasnic , Mark Connolly, Tope
Ogadeyi, Rhys Bennett, Dino Fazlic and Tom Eckersley were
released after their deals expired, the club said.   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  